  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Mandatory reporting of large transactions\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Key Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial Crime Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n5. Compliance Obligations\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential business license revocation\n- Personal liability for executives\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
